# Time Series Aggregation Tool

## Overview

The Time Series Aggregation Tool is a web-based application developed using Python and Flask. It allows users to load time-series machine metrics data, configure aggregation rules, execute aggregation jobs, and view results through a simple web interface.

The application supports multiple database systems and provides configurable aggregation intervals for processing large volumes of time-series data efficiently.

---

## Features

### Data Source Support
- SQLite
- MySQL
- PostgreSQL
- MongoDB 

### Aggregation Functions
The application supports standard aggregation operations such as:

- Sum
- Average
- Minimum
- Maximum
- Count
- First Value
- Last Value
- Median
- Standard Deviation
- Variance

### Time Bucket Support
Users can aggregate data into:

- 1 Minute
- 5 Minutes
- 15 Minutes
- 30 Minutes
- 1 Hour
- 4 Hours
- 12 Hours
- 1 Day

### Additional Features
- Property mapping configuration
- Source and target database selection
- Job execution tracking
- Aggregation history
- Data preview
- REST API endpoints
- JSON-based configuration storage

---

